ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project analyzes wetland changes in Loktak Lake, Manipur (India) using Normalized Difference Water Index (NDWI) derived from Landsat-8 satellite imagery. Seasonal comparisons (Summer & Monsoon) were performed between 2019â€“2024 to study water spread dynamics.

The workflow includes:

Preprocessing Landsat bands (Green & NIR).

Computing NDWI = (Green â€“ NIR) / (Green + NIR).

Applying a fixed threshold to generate water masks.

Comparing seasonal and temporal changes in wetland area.

Generating NDWI maps, water masks, and time-series plots.



